[size=16pt][b]DFMP: Anti-Whale Fair Mining[/b][/size]

One of Dilithion's unique features is the Dynamic Fair Mining Protocol (DFMP) -- a consensus-level system that prevents mining centralization:

[list]
[li][b]Heat System:[/b] Miners who find many blocks in a 360-block window (~24 hours) accumulate "heat" which exponentially increases their mining difficulty. Small miners below the free tier mine at standard difficulty with zero penalties.[/li]
[li][b]Maturity Period:[/b] New miner identities face a maturity penalty (2x difficulty decaying over 400 blocks), preventing rapid Sybil identity rotation.[/li]
[li][b]Registration PoW:[/b] Creating a new mining identity requires a one-time proof-of-work (28-bit SHA3), preventing mass identity generation.[/li]
[li][b]Dual-Layer Tracking:[/b] Both miner identity AND payout address are tracked. Rotating either does not bypass penalties.[/li]
[li][b]Dynamic Scaling:[/b] The free tier automatically adjusts based on the number of active miners. More miners = tighter limits for whales.[/li]
[/list]

[b]The result:[/b] A whale miner with 100 threads faces exponentially harder difficulty, while a small miner with 4-8 threads mines at standard difficulty with full 49 DIL rewards. Fair by design, enforced by code.

